title: WGP Monkey Hill Time Trial
description: Kick-off event for the Wilmington Grand Prix featuring professional and amateur racers taking on a scenic but challenging course through Brandywine Park. Event includes craft beer tasting, food trucks and live music.
course: A 3.2-mile, rolling course which finishes up the Monkey Hill Cobblestones, first made famous by the Tour DuPont.
registration:
PRE-REGISTRATION ONLY! Check-in opens @ 4pm.
Registration closes May, 13th at midnight.
For more info, go to our website, www.wilmgrandprix.com   
EVENT HELD RAIN or SHINE*
notes:
Riders sent off by category at 1/2 minute intervals (1 min for Pros).
*ALL USCF RULES APPLY
directions:
DIRECTIONS: From I-95 N or S, take US 202/Concord Pike exit. Proceed south on Rt. 202/Concord Pike, right onto Baynard Blvd., right onto 18th St.
START/FINISH across from Warner Elementary School, 801 W. 18th St., Wilmington, DE 19802
Parking at the Start/Finish area. Warm-up north of the starting area, roads open to traffic.

title: Wilmington Grand Prix
description: The 9th Annual Wilmington Grand Prix is the fifth stop on USA Cycling's National Race Calendar. Event features pro-am races, a time trial, Gran Fondo and six-block street festival.
course: One-mile, eight-corner, figure 8 downtown criterium course with a slight rise into the finish.
registration:
Limit: Six Riders per Pro Team. Day Of Registration will be available:
$10 day-of fee, Cat 5 one-day license is $15.00. Sign-in and day-of registration will be held at The Grand (818 Market Street, Wilm., DE 19801). Sign-in opens two hours prior to the start of racing; closes 15 minutes prior to the event. Registration at www.bikereg.com closes May 13 @ 5pm
notes: Neutral Support by SRAM. Free lap rule in effect. Event held rain or shine.

title: Wilmington Gran Fondo
description: A bucket-list ride through world-class attractions of the Brandywine Valley.
course: Ride begins and ends at Delaware Art Museum and passes through more than a dozen world-class cultural attractions. Significant hill climbs during medio and gran fondo. Course distances: 15 miles, 50K and 100k. Two timed climbs on the 100K course with prizes to age category winners. Mass start at 8am
registration:
Registration fees increase at end of each month. To register visit:
https://www.bikereg.com/delawaregranfondo.
directions:
Registration and start at Delaware Art Museum. 
2301 Kentmere Parkway, Wilm., DE 19086

title: River Towns Time Trial & Delaware State Championship
description: Third annual 10-mile time trial between two historic Delaware river towns with post-race festival in both towns. Final race of season for MATTS (Mid-Alantic Time Trial Series).
course:
10-mile course that is flat and fast from Historic New Castle to Historic Delaware City. All riders park in Delaware City and will do a 10-MILE warm-up ride to Official Start at Historic New Castle. Roads open to traffic.

FINISH LINE: Clinton Street, Delaware City (adjacent to Battery Park).
registration: Pre-registration only at https://www.bikereg.com/deep-blue-time-trial-matt-series-event. Registration closes Sept. 30.
notes:
Riders sent off by category at 1/2 minute intervals. Starting line: Historic New Castle. Finish line: Battery Park in Historic Delaware City.

* ALL USCF RULES APPLY * HELD UNDER USA CYCLING EVENT PERMIT
directions:
DIRECTIONS: From I-95 North or South, take DE 1 South via exit 4A (Christiana Mall). Follow 8 miles to exit 152, SR72. Follow SR72 to Delaware City. 

RIDER PARKING: All riders use parking lot on Washington Street Delaware City (adjacent to Crabby Dick’s Restaurant). As you enter Delaware City from north, make left onto Washington Street and proceed to end of the street (parking lot will be on your left).
